1 (f) (1) Unless provided by the MDEC system, the prosecuting attorney shall
2 send a victim or victim’s representative prior notice of each court proceeding in the case, of
3 the terms of any plea agreement, and of the right of the victim or victim’s representative to
4 submit a victim impact statement to the court under § 11–402 of this title if:
5 (i) prior notice is practicable; and
6 (ii) the victim or victim’s representative has filed a notification
7 request form or followed the MDEC system protocol under subsection (e) of this section.
8 (2) (i) If the case is in a jurisdiction in which the office of the clerk of
9 the circuit court or juvenile court has an automated filing system, the prosecuting attorney
10 may ask the clerk to send the notice required by paragraph (1) of this subsection.
11 (ii) If the case is in a jurisdiction that has implemented the MDEC
12 system, the victim may follow the MDEC system protocol to receive notice by electronic
13 mail, to notify the prosecuting attorney, and to request additional notice available through
14 the State’s Victim Information and Notification Everyday vendor.
15 (3) As soon after a proceeding as practicable, the prosecuting attorney shall
16 tell the victim or victim’s representative of the terms of any plea agreement, judicial action,
17 and proceeding that affects the interests of the victim or victim’s representative, including
18 a bail hearing, change in the defendant’s pretrial release order, dismissal, nolle prosequi,
19 stetting of charges, trial, disposition, and postsentencing court proceeding if:
20 (i) the victim or victim’s representative has filed a notification
21 request form or followed the MDEC system protocol under subsection (e) of this section and
22 prior notice to the victim or victim’s representative is not practicable; or
23 (ii) the victim or victim’s representative is not present at the
24 proceeding.
25 (4) Whether or not the victim or victim’s representative has filed a
26 notification request form or followed the MDEC system protocol under subsection (e) of this
27 section, the prosecuting attorney may give the victim or victim’s representative information
28 about the status of the case if the victim or victim’s representative asks for the information.
29 (5) WHETHER OR NOT THE VICTIM OR VICTIM’S REPRESENTATIVE
30 HAS FILED A NOTIFICATION REQUEST FORM OR FOLLOWED THE MDEC SYSTEM
31 PROTOCOL UNDER SUBSECTION (E) OF THIS SECTION, IF THE INDIVIDUAL IS A
32 VICTIM OF A CRIME UNDER § 7–104(G)(2) OR (3) OF THE CRIMINAL LAW ARTICLE,
33 THE PROSECUTING ATTORNEY SHALL NOTIFY THE VICTIM OR THE VICTIM’S
34 REPRESENTATIVE OF:
35 (I) EACH COURT PROCEEDING RELATED TO THE CASE;

