1 (II) THE RIGHT OF THE VICTIM TO SUBMIT A VICTIM IMPACT
2 STATEMENT;
3 (III) ANY POSTTRIAL COURT PROCEEDINGS RELATED TO THE
4 CASE;
5 (IV) ANY APPEAL RELATED TO THE CASE; AND
6 (V) ANY SENTENCE REVIEW RELATED TO THE CASE.
7 (g) If a victim or victim’s representative has filed a notification request form or
8 followed the MDEC system protocol under subsection (e) of this section, the clerk of the
9 circuit court or juvenile court:
10 (1) shall include a copy of the form with any commitment order or
11 probation order that is passed or electronically transmit the form or the registration
12 information for the victim or the victim’s representative through the MDEC system; and
13 (2) if an appeal is filed, shall send a copy of the form or electronically
14 transmit the form or the registration information for the victim or the victim’s
15 representative through the MDEC system to the Attorney General and the court to which
16 the case has been appealed.
17 (h) This section does not prohibit a victim or victim’s representative from filing a
18 notification request form with a unit to which a defendant or child respondent has been
19 committed.
20 (i) (1) After filing a notification request form under subsection (e) of this
21 subsection OR RECEIVING NOTIFICATION UNDER SUBSECTION (F)(5) OF THIS
22 SECTION, a victim or victim’s representative may discontinue further notices by filing a
23 written request with:
24 (i) the prosecuting attorney, if the case is still in a circuit court or
25 juvenile court; or
26 (ii) the unit to which the defendant or child respondent has been
27 committed, if a commitment order has been issued in the case.
28 (2) After following the MDEC system protocol for electronic notices, a
29 victim or victim’s representative may discontinue further notices by following the MDEC
30 system protocol to terminate notice.
31 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
